<TITLE> Ex-power minister's family sent to jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 3 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Tuesday sent former state minister for power Iqbal Hasan Mahmud Tuku's wife Romana Mahmud and their daughter Sara Hasin Mahmud and son Abed Hasan Mahmud to jail in a corruption case. Police Tuesday arrested Romana and Sara Hasin after an arrest warrant against them in a corruption case with Mohammadpur Police Station. Later in the day, Abed Hasan turned himself in to court. After a hearing, the court ordered the three to jail. Mohammadpur police arrested Tuku's wife and daughter at around 2pm from 1/7 Asad Avenue, a security guard of the house, Mojibur Rahman, said. Mohammadpur police duty officer, sub-inspector Jahangir Hossain, told bdnews24.com, "They were arrested under a court warrant in a corruption case." The arrestees were produced at 4pm before Dhaka metropolitan senior special Judge Md Azizul Haq's court. At the same time, Tuku's son surrendered to court. Assistant director Shahriar Chowdhury of the Anticorruption Commission filed the case against Tuku's wife, daughter and son, charging them with suppressing details in their wealth statements. bdnews24.com
